metadata.intent: patient wants to know about clinic services
metadata.information: Urgent Care Services, Primary Care, Diagnostic Services, Specialized Testing, Childrens Services, Preventive Health

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about urgent care services at the clinic
metadata.information: Urgent Care Services - Treatment for ER diagnoses, Walk-ins and appointments accepted, Telemedicine visits available

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about primary care services at the clinic
metadata.information: Wellness checks, Annual physicals, Chronic disease management, On-site X-ray, On-site EKG

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Diagnostic services at the clinic
metadata.information: Digital X-ray (mentioned twice), On-site lab testing, Flu tests, Urine tests, TB shots

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Specialized Testing at the clinic
metadata.information: STD testing and treatment

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Childrens Services at the clinic
metadata.information: Childrens urgent care, School, camp, and sports physicals

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Preventive Health Services at the clinic
metadata.information: Routine checkups, Seasonal allergy treatments

metadata.intent: patient wants to know aboutkinds of physicals are available at the clinic
metadata.information: General Physicals, Pre-employment Physicals

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about screening done in the clinc
metadata.information: Drug Screenings, Vision Testing, TB Testing (One-step, Two-step) Labs

metadata.intent: patient wants to know what is included in the physicals
metadata.information: Drug Screenings, Vision Testing, TB Testing (One-step, Two-step), Vital signs (blood pressure, heart rate, temperature), Heart and lung health, Abdominal health, Skin for signs of underlying illness

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about what condition is treated at UCOK Mental Health Center
metadata.information: Depression, Anxiety, PTSD, ADHD, Addiction, Eating Disorders, Sleep/Insomnia, Anger, Bipolar Disorder, Chronic Pain, Relationship Issues, Parenting, Grief, Self-Harm, Substance Abuse, Emotional Disturbance, School Issues, Internet/Gaming/Gambling Addiction, and more.

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Therapies and Services Offered at the clinic
metadata.information: marriage counseling, family therapy, and help with divorce and relationship issues,  ADHD, behavioral issues, school issues, learning disabilities

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about types of wounds treated at the clinic
metadata.information: Cuts and lacerations, Abrasions, Burns, Surgical wounds, Pressure ulcers, Skin infections

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about appointment for wound care
metadata.information: You need schedule an appointment but it is not necessary. We welcome walk-ins during business hours for same-day wound care.

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Insurance.
metadata.information: Urgent Care of Kansas accepts most insurances including Medicare and Medicaid. Feel free to ask us about acceptance of your insurance. We offer competitive rates and accept cash and major credit cards.

metadata.intent: patient wants to know about Self-Pay
metadata.information: We offer straightforward self-pay pricing so patients can receive quality care without surprise costs. There are lots of things you worry about when it comes to your health care, but the price shouldnt be one of them.
